I joke a lot about having social anxiety, but I am literally constantly on guard when I’m in public. Every time a stranger approaches me and I can tell they’re about to say something to me my brain says “here we go…”

The other day someone I met told me they’d never been friends with someone like me, but they knew I was a human being. Like WHAT? And the crazy thing is people genuinely don’t mean harm when they say things like this.

And it affects how people like me are perceived by everyone else. I got strangers asking me to take pictures with them, taking pictures of me without my permission, or asking me to shake their hands because they’re under the impression that seeing me is an experience.

I went my whole life being told by movies/television people who look like me are only good for comedic value or being cast as mythical creatures. Like dang, I can’t be a love interest? I can’t be a superhero? I can’t just be a regular character in a movie?
